{"title": "The great squandering of American power", "tags": "opinion", "timestamp": "2024-10-04", "content": "Realists and Pax Americana sceptics may call me naive, but I have long placed my faith in the rules-based international order so fervently championed by Washington and its allies.\nThere have been ups and downs \u2013 particularly during the turbulent days of Donald Trump\u2019s presidency \u2013 but never a genuine crisis of belief in this order as the best framework for maintaining peace and containing conflict."}